files.Title: QoreDB.StorageEngine.Pager.BasePager
files.Summary: Provides a base implementation for a pager that manages reading and writing pages to an underlying stream, with an integrated LRU (Least Recently Used) caching mechanism. This class is abstract and must be inherited by a concrete pager implementation that provides the specific stream (e.g., FileStream or MemoryStream).

files.Title: QoreDB.StorageEngine.Pager.InMemoryQorePager
files.Summary: A concrete pager implementation that uses an in-memory stream for data storage. This is useful for temporary databases or for unit testing the storage engine without hitting the file system.

files.Title: QoreDB.StorageEngine.Pager.Interfaces.IPager
files.Summary: Defines the core contract for a pager component, which is responsible for reading and writing fixed-size pages to and from an underlying data stream. This interface abstracts the direct interaction with the data source.

files.Title: QoreDB.StorageEngine.Pager.Models.QorePage
files.Summary: Represents a single, fixed-size page of data held in memory. This class acts as the unit of transfer between the storage engine and the in-memory cache.

files.Title: QoreDB.StorageEngine.Pager.QorePager
files.Summary: A concrete pager implementation that uses a physical file on disk for data storage. This pager is responsible for persisting data between application sessions.
